1 No out-of-school or summer program providing child care pursuant to this section shall care for
2 more than 25 children in one group. The out-of-school or summer program providing care for 26
3 or more children shall provide for two or more groups according to the ages of children and shall
4 provide separate supervisory personnel.
5 SECTION 1.9.(c) When an individual who has received a provisional credential
6 pursuant to this section reaches 18 years of age and has obtained a high school diploma or its
7 equivalent, the individual shall notify the Division of Child Development and Early Education
8 (Division) of such, if they wish to receive the full Early Childhood Credential, and the Division
9 shall issue the individual the full North Carolina Early Childhood Credential which shall enable
10 that individual to be employed as a lead teacher in any licensed child care program in this State.
11
12 PART II. CHILD CARE MENTAL AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES
13 FUNDING
14 SECTION 2.1.(a) There is appropriated from the ARPA Temporary Savings Fund,
15 established in Section 1.3(a) of S.L. 2023-7, to the Department of Health and Human Services,
16 Division of Child Development and Early Education, the sum of fifteen million dollars
17 ($15,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be allocated to the North
18 Carolina Partnership for Children, Inc. (NCPC), to expand mental and behavioral health services
19 for children, families, and staff in child care facility settings and out-of-school programs,
20 including on-site services and behavioral health supports. The NCPC shall spend the funds
21 appropriated in this Part in the following budget codes: PSC 5415 Health Care Access and
22 Support, PSC 5505 Parent Education, PSC 3125 Quality Child Care, and PSC 5509 Parents as
23 Teachers. The NCPC shall distribute the funds appropriated in this Part to local partnerships, as
24 determined by the NCPC. These funds shall supplement and not supplant existing Smart Start
25 partnership behavioral health spending. Funds appropriated in this Part shall not revert at the end
26 of the 2026-2027 fiscal year but shall remain available for costs associated with mental and
27 behavioral health initiatives described in this subsection until expended.
28 SECTION 2.1.(b) The NCPC shall submit a progress report on the mental and
29 behavioral health initiatives described in subsection (a) of this section to the Joint Legislative
30 Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services, the Secretary of the Department of Health
31 and Human Services, and the Fiscal Research Division by March 15, 2027, and a final report by
32 November 15, 2028. The progress report and final report shall include all of the following:
33 (1) The name of each local partnership that received funds.
34 (2) The number of children served by each local partnership.
35 (3) The types of mental and behavioral health services provided by each local
36 partnership.
37 (4) Recommendations for continuing and/or expanding mental and behavioral
38 health initiatives for children, families, and staff in child care facility settings.
39 SECTION 2.1.(c) Additional funds allocated in this Part to the North Carolina
40 Partnership for Children, Inc., from the Department of Health and Human Services, Division of
41 Child Development and Early Education, for the 2026-2027 fiscal year are not subject to the
42 administrative cost requirements under Section 9D.5(b) of S.L. 2023-134, child care services
43 funding requirements under G.S. 143B-168.15(b), child care subsidy expansion requirements
44 under G.S. 143B-168.15(g), or match requirements under Section 9D.5(d) of S.L. 2023-134.
45 SECTION 2.2.(a) G.S. 143B-168.15(h) reads as rewritten:
46 "(h) The North Carolina Partnership for Children, Inc., Special Fund is hereby established
47 as an interest-bearing, nonreverting special fund in the Department of Health and Human
48 Services. Funds appropriated from the General Fund to the Department for Smart Start and the
49 North Carolina Partnership for Children, Inc. (NCPC), shall be deposited in the Fund and shall
50 be used by the NCPC and local partnerships exclusively for the purposes authorized in this
51 section, unless otherwise expressly provided by law. State funds allocated to local partnerships
